Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ui: disable the native horizontal tab strip

Removes the BrowserView horizontal TabStrip from the browser chrome so
it can be replaced by the Fennec vertical sidebar (see
vertical-sidebar-scaffold.patch). Without this patch, both the native
strip and the sidebar would be visible simultaneously.

Approach (mirrors Zen Browser's Firefox patch):
  1. Set TabStrip visibility to hidden via BrowserView::Layout()
  2. Suppress the tab strip height reservation in BrowserViewLayout
  3. Keep the TabStripModel alive — tab management logic is unchanged;
     only the visual strip is hidden

TODO: Stub. Full implementation in Phase 2.
      Tracked: fennec-browser/fennec#10

PILLAR: Calm UI
JOURNAL: none
